      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The distributive property is a fundamental concept in algebra that helps you isolate the variable x in equations. It's particularly useful when dealing with negative numbers, as it allows you to distribute the negative sign to the terms inside the parentheses. For example, if you have an equation like -3(x + 2) = 12, you can use the distributive property to simplify it to -3x - 6 = 12. This helps you solve for x by getting rid of the parentheses and isolating the variable.",
